==English==

===Etymology===
Hebrew אבנר (Abner), meaning "father of [or is a] light". From אָב (av = 'father') + נור (nur = 'light'). Cf. Eleanor.

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Abner'''

# [[Cousin]] of [[Saul]] in the [[Old Testament]].

